Step 1: Create a Security Group for the NAT Instance

The NAT instance needs to accept traffic from your private subnets and send it out to the internet.

1.Go to the EC2 Dashboard.
2.On the left menu, scroll down to Network & Security and click Security Groups.
3.Click Create security group.
4.Name: finops-nat-sg.
5.Description: Security group for NAT instance.
6.VPC: Select your finops-project VPC.
7.Inbound Rules: * Click Add rule.
                   Type: All traffic.
                   Source: Custom, and type in your VPC's CIDR block (e.g., 10.0.0.0/16). This allows all instances in your VPC to send traffic to the NAT instance.
8.Outbound Rules: Leave as default (All traffic to 0.0.0.0/0).
