6.Block Public Access settings: Keep Block all public access CHECKED. (This is a security best practice; later, we will explicitly allow only our CloudFront CDN to read these images).
7.Scroll to the bottom and click Create bucket.

Apply the intelligent-tiering Rule :
1.Click on your newly created buket name 
2.Go to the Management tab.
3.Under Lifecycle rules,click create Lifecycle rule
4.Lifecycle rule name: Move-To-Intelligent-Tiering.
5.Rule scope: Select Apply to all objects in the bucket. (Check the acknowledgment box that appears).
6.LifeCycle rule actions: Checkc Trasition current version of objects between storage classes
7.Under Transition current versions of objects, select Intelligent-Tiering from the dropdown, and enter 0 for "Days after object creation". (This means files go straight to FinOps storage the moment they are uploaded).
