Phase 4: The  DR setup 

Part 1: S3 cross region replication (CRR)

To copy your data automatically, AWS requires a destination bucket in a different region, and both the source and destination buckets must have Versioning enabled.

Step 1.1: Create the DR Bucket

1.Navigate to the S3 console.
2.Click Create bucket.
3.AWS Region: Select your secondary region (e.g., Oregon - us-west-2).
4.Bucket Versioning: Select Enable. (Crucial: Replication will not work without this).
5.Leave everything else as default and click Create bucket.

Step 1.2:  Enable Versioning on the Primary Bucket

1.Click on your primary bucket created in Phase 2 (e.g., finops-ecommerce-assets-yourinitials in us-east-1).
2.Go to the Properties tab.
3.Under Bucket Versioning, click Edit, select Enable, and click Save changes.

Step 1.3: Create the Replication Rule 

1.Still inside your primary bucket, click the Management tab.
2.Scroll down to Replication rules and click Create replication rule.
3.Replication rule name: DR-Copy-To-West.
4.Status: Keep it Enabled.
5.Choose a rule scope: Select Apply to all objects in the bucket.
6.Destination: Select Specify a bucket in another AWS Region. Enter the name of your DR bucket (finops-ecommerce-dr-assets-yourinitials).
7.IAM role: Select Create new role. AWS will automatically generate the permissions needed for S3 to read from the primary bucket and write to the DR bucket.
8.Click Save. (When asked if you want to replicate existing objects, choose No, do not replicate existing objects for this exercise to keep it simple, as it requires a batch operations job).


Part 2: Automated RDS snapshots with AWS backup

Writing custom Lambda scripts for database backups is tedious. AWS Backup is a centralized service that fully automates this, including the cross-region copying.


step 2.1: Create the Backup Plan

1.:Navigate to the AWS Backup service using the top search bar.
2.On the left menu, click Backup plans, then click Create backup plan.
3.Select Build a new plan.
4.Backup plan name: FinOps-Pilot-Light-DR.

Step 2.2: Configure the backup Rule

1.Scroll down to Backup rule configuration
2.Rule name: Daily-Cross-Region-Backup.
3.Backup vault: Select Default (or create a new one).
4.Backup frequency: Select Daily.
5.Backup window: Select Use default backup window (runs overnight to minimize database performance impact).
6.Lifecycle: Set Transition to cold storage to Never, and Expire to 7 days. (As part of a FinOps strategy, we must aggressively expire old snapshots so they don't become costly "zombie resources" sitting unattached in our account).
7.Copy to destination: * Destination Region: Select your DR region (e.g., US West (Oregon)).


--Destination Backup vault: Click Create new backup vault, name it DR-Vault, and click Create.
--Expand Advanced settings under the copy section. Set the copied snapshot to also Expire after 7 days.

8.Create the plan 

Step 2.3: Assign the Database to the Plan

1.You will immediately be prompted to Assign resources.
2.Resource assignment name: CloudBite-DB-Assignment.
3.IAM role: Select Default role.
4.Assign by: Select Resource ID.
5.Resource type: Select RDS.
6.Database: Select your finops-ecommerce-db.
7.Click Assign resources.

